## Live tail streaming

- **`useSocketStream`** (`src/shared/hooks/useSocketStream.ts`) ‚Äî core WebSocket to `/api/v1/ws/live`: connection, dedup, lag, drop tracking. Status: idle ‚Üí connecting ‚Üí live ‚Üí closed/error
- **`useLiveTailStream`** (`src/features/explorer-core/hooks/useLiveTailStream.ts`) ‚Äî wrapper injecting `teamId`; accepts `subscribeEvent`, `itemEvent`, `params`, `maxItems`
- Protocol: `{op: "subscribe:logs", ...params}` ‚Üí server streams `{event: "log", data: ...}` + heartbeat every 15s
- Used by: Logs domain (`useLogsHubData`)

## Global refresh / auto-refresh

- **Zustand:** `src/app/store/appStore.ts` ‚Äî `triggerRefresh()` increments **`refreshKey`** (manual/auto refresh only; time-range changes do not bump it).
- **Persisted state:** `selectedTeamId`, `timeRange`, `autoRefreshInterval`, `theme`, `timezone`, `comparisonMode`, `viewPreferences`, `recentPages`, `recentTimeRanges`
- **Runtime state:** `refreshKey`
- **TanStack Query:** **Do not** put `refreshKey` in `queryKey` (it creates a new cache entry every tick and blinks the UI). Use **`timeRangeQuerySegment(timeRange)`** in keys and call **`resolveTimeRangeBounds(timeRange)`** inside **`queryFn`** so relative windows slide on refetch. **`QueryLifecycleBridge`** invalidates queries whose key includes the selected team id when `refreshKey` bumps. Use **`placeholderData: keepPreviousData`** where appropriate.
- **Backend-driven dashboard panels** (`useComponentDataFetcher`): stable keys with `timeRangeQuerySegment`; treat **loading** as `isPending && data === undefined`.

